Developing an automated weekly report to extract all users and groups across Cohesity clusters, including cluster-level mapping and a consolidated view of unique users and groups. The report will provide standardized visibility across environments for access review.

Purpose
To establish a centralized and consistent view of user and group access across all clusters, enabling periodic validation of access alignment and identification of unauthorized or stale accounts.

Benefits

Enables scheduled (weekly) access governance with minimal manual effort

Improves visibility of user/group distribution across clusters

Facilitates identification of misaligned or excessive access

Supports audit and compliance requirements with consistent reporting

Reduces risk from inactive or unnecessary accounts

Why This Is Required
Access changes are dynamic across clusters, and lack of centralized tracking can lead to privilege creep, orphaned accounts, and audit gaps. A scheduled report ensures continuous monitoring, traceability, and proactive access control validationUpdate Summary

